<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900628-0051</DOCNO><DOCID>900628-0051.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Mellon Bank Corp.:   Consolidation of Charters   Sought for Banking Units</HL><DATE>06/28/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MEL</CO><IN>BANKS (BNK)</IN><LP>   Mellon Bank Corp., Pittsburgh, said it filed applicationswith the comptroller of the currency to consolidate thecharters of its five Pennsylvania banks.   The bank holding company said the move would simplify itscorporate financial and legal structure, and enable customersto cash checks and do all banking at any of the 353 MellonBank branch offices statewide. The company said the movewouldn't affect the management structure, boards or employeesof the banks.</LP><TEXT>   Mellon said these banks would be consolidated into asingle bank called Mellon Bank N.A.: Commonwealth NationalBank, Harrisburg; Mellon Bank (Central), State College;Mellon Bank (East), Philadelphia; Mellon Bank, Pittsburgh;and Mellon Bank (North), Oil City. Mellon also said it plansto change Commonwealth National Bank's name to Mellon Bank.The company expects the consolidation to be completed byearly next year.</TEXT></DOC>